<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-17T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/2112: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-17T19:00:00-05:00">March 17, 1938—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>82. Your 175, March 16, 5 p.m., in regard to the Fan Biological Institute
                            at Peiping. The Department perceives no objection to your taking, orally
                            and informally, the action suggested.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>